content: Praps ok for American use not suitable for uk.
Trying to load generates error message "App Corrupted". Seeking refund from developers.
Won't open. Says data corrupted. Repeatedly. Want a refund immediately!
App doesn't work. Downloaded and installed 3 times. Crashes, never loads.
Doesn't work on my Pixel 5 - please refund!
Worst android app I ever used. This app is keep on crashing after recording. I need my money back. For others who read this, do not waste your money.(I am using a Note 9)
Not for South Africa
I tried to download it several times it says that the data is corrupted- never worked. I'm asking for a refund And we'll try other similar apps.
Every time in try to use this, it crashes. I was excited to use this but haven't been able to.
Difficult to use. Adds numerous and unwanted images to my phone.
Hundreds of bird calls were automatically downloaded into my music library without my knowing it. And it hadn't helped me make one identification yet.
App wouldn't open. ( I paid for it! ) Avoid this app
This app is a joke Don't waste your money. Wish I had read the comments before I downloaded it.
Won't load. Can't answer any questions about it
When it comes to the final identify process. It shuts down and the customer support is only reaches through email. For an app that cost money AND doesn't work its was a waste
Crashes constantly and makes ridiculous match suggestions. Love the way it records the 1.5 seconds before pushing record. Really wanted it to work. What a waste.
Great if you find Northern Mockingbirds everywhere. I can be looking at any bird while recording, and it comes up the same every time. That is if the app doesn't crash.

On Galaxy S10+, every time I touched the screen to start recording bird songs or to identify birds, a picture was generated in my phone library resulting in hundreds of pictures of sound recordings and some kind of strange rendition of a bird. Not worth the effort to have to delete.
I couldn't get the app to work it crashed five times each time I recorded a birds song.
This app would be awesome if it didn't constantly crash.
Crashed the first time I used it when I went to "match songs". Exception handling, people!
This app constantly crashes, not once has it worked no matter how clear the recording. A complete waste of money!
Keeps closing on me..almost never IDs bird correctly

Its cool, the auto comes out good. But when ever i try to match a auto with a bird it says " BirdGenie is not working right " and i always have to close the app. Its a good idea. But the bugs with it are really inraging.
crashes often, too hard to select song to be of use
App is very poor, keeps on crashing. Have rebooted my phone, still wont work.
Crashes
Crashes, stops and closes. Can not identify birds
This app would not even open up on my phone
It's practically shut my cellphone down and I'd appreciate if you would give me a credit for the $3.99 you charged to my visa card.
Dont like privacy policy.
No way to set it for UK. Uninstalled.
identifies birds with calls completly different than my recording

Did an okay job - Developer bug clutters photo folder big time by not self containing all image files and sound files to a dedicated folder. Instead it created a hundred folders within my root image and sound folders... Incredibly annoying!

Very cool idea, but no way to help the app learn if it asks the same questions over and over, and presents the same potential matches. I know for a fact I was listening to an Eastern Whipbird, but try telling the app it wasn't a dang Crackle. Come up with some new birds, Princeton!

I didnt even have a chance to try it out. I had to uninstall because if the ridiculous way it overtook my phones photo gallery. I couldnt find anything in there anymore except what it dumped in there. It was absolutely ridiculous. Just what a person wants when they ooen their photo gallery is to habe to wade through a hundred photos of vouce recordings of birds. Terrible design flaw, i expected better with it coming out of a university.
First app I ever purchased. Crashes nearly every use and hasn't help me id any birds by song.
Always crashes.
the app keeps stopping and doesn't work after recording and the few recordings that were made did not match the correct bird
App filled my drive with unreauested photos and then never once correctly identified a bird
this app needs a lot of work. does not ID birds 99% of the time and crashes every time in use it. disappointed to say the least.

Not nearly enough species in the database, and the ones that are there are so common most birders would know them in a second . In addition, I played three bird songs from my Merlin Bird app in the quiet of my kitchen right next to the app and it could not identify a single bird. To make matters worse the app uploaded over 400 images into my gallery, I would reconsider the app when they have a full database of birds.
crashes every use. totally unusable on my android phone, a waste of space and four bucks.

I can't believe that I PAID for this app. Every time I tried to use it, the app shut down after recording the birds. Plus, my gallery filled up with sound recordings and bird pictures. Very upsetting.
useless for bird id
Good idea but the app requires a lot of work. No ability to sync to cloud. Can't set UK as location. Random and frequent crashes.
Downloaded recently and once I have the recording sonogram and hit "match", I just get an error stating that the app had stopped working. Happens EVERYTIME
There arent enough birds listed in app for it to match with. Needs more variety.
Oh, no, no, no. Absolutely not! I spent 30 minutes outside today and had to delete 420(!!!!) images that the app added to my Gallery (unbeknownst to me). The app has been deleted.

very disappointing. tried with: Canada geese protecting their nest. mourning doves, & cardinal. not even close on any of them. was within 10 - 20 feet of the birds with little to no background noise. recorded ok but identification was not accurate. kept giving sparrows and mockingbirds.
Crashes 2 or 3 times before you get to the match option. Then pretty poor in identifying bird.

I am uninstalling this ap. No matter how close, crystal clear and beautiful a recording I obtained, I NEVER got a match. On top of that, the images from the app populated my gallery in an intrusive way that seemed impossible to remedy! Enough. Cumbersome and useless. So sad, I had dreamed of an app like this for years, just one that worked. and argh!! after removing the app, the distorted images are still there and I need to search them out and delete manually.
Won't download and haven't found a way to get assistance. frustrating.
Promising approach but not quite ready for prime time. App is slow to open and crashes often.
The app routinely shuts down when you select certain options from the menu. In addition it has routinely failed to identify a common bird species correctly. Still needs work.
Won't download. Tried three times. Keeps hanging. On high speed wifi and plenty of room on phone. Really wanted this app. Submitting for refund.
